{{Transcript list|Cassius|Gillie Groats|Seth Groats|Duke Horacio}}

==Starting off==
* '''Cassius:''' You!
* '''Player:''' Me?
* '''Cassius:''' Yes you!
* '''Player:''' Can I... help you?
* '''Cassius:''' That depends. Do you like making money?
* '''Player:''' I'm not averse to making money.
* '''Cassius:''' And do you enjoy... milk?
* '''Player:''' Milk?
* '''Cassius:''' Milk.
* {{tcond|If the player is on a quest speedrunning world:}}
** '''Player:''' I suppose it's okay.
** '''Cassius:''' Well, fair enough. If your passion for milk changes, let me know.
** {{tbox|This quest is not available on Speedrunning Worlds.}}
** {{Tact|end}}
* '''Player:''' I can't say I've thought much about it.
* '''Cassius:''' Would you like to think more about it?
* {{tbox|Before starting this quest, be aware that your combat level is lower than the recommended level of 15.}}
* {{tselect|Start The Ides of Milk quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Player:''' What am I going to get from thinking more about... milk?
** '''Cassius:''' Profit!
** '''Cassius:''' Ten to fifteen percent, performance depending.
** '''Player:''' How are we going to be making that profit? And who even are you anyway?
** '''Cassius:''' Ah, my name is Cassius. I got carried away.
** '''Cassius:''' But, we're going to construct an empire.
** '''Player:''' Of milk?
** '''Cassius:''' Of milk.
** '''Player:''' How do you intend to make an empire of milk?
** '''Cassius:''' So, the first step is going to involve you doing a little... research.
** '''Player:''' Right...
** '''Cassius:''' You're going to cross the River Lum, find Gillie and Seth Groats, and learn about animal husbandry.
** '''Cassius:''' Then... Then you're going to cross back to this side of the river, and tell me all about how they've made their animals so productive.
** '''Cassius:''' It's a perfect plan!
** '''Player:''' What use is it if I know everything and you don't? Couldn't I make my own... milk empire... with that information?
** '''Player:''' If anything I should be cutting you in at ten to fifteen percent.
** '''Cassius:''' Hey, I'm the one supplying the high-quality milk here.
** '''Cassius:''' Not to mention, my associate Brutus is already embedded in the Groats operation to work a different angle. That will prove most lucrative.
** '''Player:''' Right... I guess I'll go and see the Groatses then.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** '''Player:''' No, I'm not sure I would like that, thank you.
** {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to release the bull early===
* '''Player:''' Releasing the bull into the cow pen is a bad idea.
* {{tbox|You need to have completed The Ides of Milk quest to release this bull.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Cassius again before talking to both Gillie and Seth===
* '''Player:''' What was it you needed me to do again?
* '''Cassius:''' I need you to speak to Gillie and Seth Groats. We need to learn everything we can.
* '''Cassius:''' They live just across the River Lum. Head east from here and you should be able to find them.
* {{Tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Hello, I'm Gillie the Milkmaid. What can I do for you?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Who are you?|quest=no}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me how to milk a cow?|quest=no}}
* {{topt|Can you share what makes your cows so productive?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you share what makes your cows so productive?
** '''Gillie Groats:''' Absolutely! The secret is happiness.
** '''Player:''' Happiness?
** '''Gillie Groats:''' The cows make the best milk when they're happy, and to be honest, they make too much!
** '''Gillie Groats:''' I'm always glad that adventurers come by and help with milking them. I wouldn't be able to keep up otherwise.
** '''Player:''' That can't be everything though, can it?
** '''Gillie Groats:''' Come to think of it, I'm sure my father keeps a few tricks up his sleeve. Why don't you go and ask him?
** {{tcond|If the player has not yet talked to Seth Groats:}}
*** '''Player:''' That would be Seth, wouldn't it?
*** '''Gillie Groats:''' It would be! I'm sure he'll he happy to share some information with you.
*** '''Player:''' I'll go and speak to him now, thank you!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has already talked to Seth Groats:}}
*** '''Player:''' I've already had a chance to talk to him. He did indeed have some tricks to share!
*** '''Gillie Groats:''' That's good. You must be ready to care for your own cows at this point!
*** '''Player:''' If you think so, then I must be. Thank you for your help, I'll make sure that knowledge is put to good use.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'm fine, thanks.|quest=no}}

===Talking to Seth===
* '''Seth Groats:''' Well well, what can I do for you?
* '''Player:''' I was wondering if you could teach me a little about how you're so successful with your animals.
* '''Seth Groats:''' Lookin' to get into the business, eh?
* '''Player:''' Something along those lines.
* '''Seth Groats:''' Well, always happy to help another budding farmer out!
* '''Player:''' Great! So where do I start?
* '''Seth Groats:''' Would always recommend me Groats Principles as yer basics.
* '''Player:''' Groats Principles?
* '''Seth Groats:''' Aye. First one is that happy animals makes happy farmers.
* '''Seth Groats:''' Second of me principles is to never take more than you need. Greed'll stop you in your tracks.
* '''Seth Groats:''' The last principle: never let the taxman know yer earnings. Money should be spent on the animals!
* {{tcond|If the player is an [[Ironman Mode|ironman]]:}}
** '''Player:''' I don't think I've ever paid any taxes.
** '''Seth Groats:''' You're ahead of the game then!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player is not an ironman:}}
** '''Player:''' You've found a way to get around the taxes?
** '''Seth Groats:''' A way or two.
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Seth Groats:''' Anyway, feel free to grab me book on the topic from the shelf over there.
* '''Player:''' Okay, thank you for the help.
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the shelf===
* {{tcond|Before learning about the book:}}
** {{mes|You find a bucket on the shelf, as you'd expect a farmer to have.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|Without free inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=The groats principles detail.png|You find Seth's book on the shelf, but don't have room to take it with you.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|With free inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=The groats principles detail.png|You find Seth's book of principles on the shelf.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|With the book already in the inventory:}}
** {{mes|You find a loose egg on the shelf, and fortunately avoid knocking it to the floor.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Seth again===
* '''Seth Groats:''' Well well, what can I do for you?
* '''Player:''' I was wondering if you could teach me a little about how you're so successful with your animals.
* '''Seth Groats:''' Mmm we already had this talk. Go read me book on the shelf over there.
* {{Tcond|If the player doesn't have the book on them:}}
** '''Player:''' I'll go grab it, thanks.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{Tcond|If the player has the book on them:}}
** '''Player:''' I've actually got it here, I'll take it away and give it a read somewhere a little more peaceful.
** {{tact|end}}

==Returning to Cassius==
* '''Cassius:''' So, how did you get on?
* '''Player:''' I've learned a lot about how the Groats family care for their animals. They say the secret is happiness!
* '''Cassius:''' Happiness?! That can't be the only trick they use! Surely you found something else?
* {{Tcond|If the player doesn't have the book on them:}}
** '''Player:''' Now that you mention it, Seth did say he had a book that I... don't have on me right now.
** '''Cassius:''' The legendary Groats book on milk cultivation? I'm most interested! Go fetch it!
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Player:''' I have this book from Seth. He claims it's got his principles of animal husbandry in it, if that's of any use?
* '''Cassius:''' Hand it here, quickly!
* {{tbox|pic=The groats principles detail.png|Cassius snatches the book from your hands.}}
* '''Cassius:''' Now, this is most curious.
* '''Cassius:''' The idea that a happy animal will do what you want is frankly absurd. What if they choose to not produce. Are you supposed to respect that?
* '''Cassius:''' However, the writings on the systems of taxation are fascinating. I couldn't imagine Seth was smart enough to put this together.
* '''Player:''' So, do you think this is enough to start our milk empire?
* '''Cassius:''' No, no. Not quite yet. First of all, you haven't tried our milk yet, have you?
* '''Player:''' I don't think I have, no. You already have some milk?
* '''Cassius:''' Don't look so worried. Here, have a try.
* {{tbox|pic=Milk sample detail.png|Cassius hands you a milk sample to try.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Destroying the milk sample===
* {{tbox|Why would you want to destroy such good milk? Do you not wish to taste it?}}
* {{tact|Continues with Destroy confirmation message}}

===Reclaiming the milk sample===
* '''Player:''' I've managed to lose that sample of milk...
* {{tcond|Without free inventory space:}}
** '''Cassius:''' I'll give you some more once you've got some space.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|With free inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Milk sample detail.png|Cassius glares as he hands you another sample of milk.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Cassius before sampling the milk===
* '''Cassius:''' Have you given that sample a try yet?
* {{tact|end}}

===After sampling the milk===
* '''Player:''' Oh, that's not good milk.
* {{tact|The player coughs and is damaged for 1 Hitpoints with a poison hitsplat.}}
* '''Player:''' That's really not good milk.
* '''Cassius:''' So, what do you think? The milk is fantastic, isn't it?
* '''Player:''' It wasn't what I was expecting, certainly.
* '''Cassius:''' We're going to change the lactic landscape! Before we do though, I have another task for you.
* '''Player:''' Now what do you need?
* '''Cassius:''' We need... a permit.
* '''Player:''' Shouldn't you have got a permit before making milk?
* '''Cassius:''' The permit is to sell milk, not to make milk!
* '''Player:''' Fine, where are we going to get this permit?
* '''Cassius:''' From the Duke of Lumbridge! Where else? You need to bring him our milk and I'm sure he'll give us our permit without fuss.
* '''Player:''' Are you sure having the Duke drink our milk is a good idea?
* '''Cassius:''' Of course! Soon the whole of Lumbridge will be drinking my, I mean our milk!
* {{tbox|pic=Milk sample detail.png|Cassius hands you a milk sample.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to drink the second sample===
* '''Player:''' I don't think I'm ready to drink another vial of this stuff.
* '''Player:''' I should find someone else to give it to.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Cassius again===
* '''Cassius:''' Has the Duke given us our permit yet?
* {{Tcond|If the player lost the second milk sample:}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet, no. I could do with another sample of milk though, if you have one spare?
** '''Cassius:''' I should have one somewhere here. Just a moment.
** {{tcond|Without free inventory space:}}
*** '''Cassius:''' It looks like you don't have space to carry this. You'll have to grab it from me when you have room.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|With free inventory space:}}
*** '''Cassius:''' I should have one somewhere here. Just a moment.
*** {{tbox|pic=Milk sample detail.png|Cassius hands you a milk sample.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{Tcond|If the player still has the second milk sample:}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet, no, but I am working on it!
** {{tact|end}}

==Talking to the Duke==
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Greetings. Welcome to my castle.
* '''Player:''' Greetings. I come seeking a business permit.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Oh wonderful! What sort of business are you looking to start?
* '''Player:''' I'm looking to get into the milk trade!
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Milk? Well, the Groats family still have their permit, and I can't start stepping on their toes.
* '''Player:''' If you'd just try this milk...
* '''Duke Horacio:''' I really couldn't possibly give you a permit without their approval. This is really their territory.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Why not speak to Gillie Groats? She seems to handle the milk side of the business now. Maybe she'll get you set up under their permit.
* '''Player:''' You're the Duke. Couldn't you just grant a permit?
* '''Duke Horacio:''' No, no. It's really quite important you speak to Gillie about this.
* '''Player:''' Aren't you the highest power in this land?
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Don't go digging too deeply into that. Even I have some... commitments that I have to keep to.
* '''Player:''' But you're the Duke, you shouldn't need the approval of a business entity to grant a permit.
* '''Player:''' Not to mention, can't they just refuse to have any competitors?
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Well absolutely, but I'm sure you'll find they're more than reasonable about things.
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Entirely. Completely reasonable.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Duke again===
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Greetings. Welcome to my castle.
* '''Player:''' Hi, what did you want me to do for the permit again?
* '''Duke Horacio:''' Go speak to Gillie Groats. She seems to handle the milk business in Lumbridge. Maybe she'll get you set up under their permit.
* '''Player:''' Thanks.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Hiya, did you need something else from me?
* '''Player:''' I did. I've been trying to secure a business permit from the Duke, but he said that as it is a milk-related business venture, I should speak to you instead.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' The Duke is a good man, directing you to me! I've been running the milk side of our farm for a while now.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Were you thinking of being a competitor to us then?
* {{Tcond|If the player doesn't have the second milk sample:}}
** '''Player:''' I can prove we wouldn't be if you could just try this sample of...
** '''Gillie Groats:''' Sample of?
** '''Player:''' I seem to have misplaced my sample of milk. I'll be back when I have it.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{Tcond|If the player has the second milk sample:}}
** '''Player:''' I think if you were to try this sample here you'd see we wouldn't be competing.
** '''Gillie Groats:''' You want me to drink a vial of mysterious liquid?
** '''Player:''' Well, it's not mysterious, it's milk!
** '''Gillie Groats:''' No, I think you should drink it, I'll know the quality of it from your reaction.
** '''Gillie Groats:''' It is just milk after all.
** '''Player:''' Would it convince you to help me with my permit?
** '''Gillie Groats:''' It definitely won't hurt your chances.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie again===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Have you tried that milk sample yet?
* '''Player:''' Not yet. I really don't want to, but I guess I must.
* {{tact|end}}

====Attempting to drink the sample while not next to Gillie====
* '''Player:''' I shouldn't drink this unless I have Gillie nearby.
* {{tact|end}}

===Drinking the second sample===
* '''Player:''' Oh, that's worse milk than before.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' That looked like a horrible experience.
* '''Player:''' It wasn't pleasant.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Where did you even get that milk?
* '''Player:''' My business partner, Cassius. I don't know where he gets it from originally though.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Cassius... I don't recognise the name. He's not mentioned anything about its source?
* '''Player:''' Nothing, but he apparently has enough of a source to start a business. I'm mostly trying to be helpful.
* '''Player:''' If the milk's bad, you're not going to recommend us for a permit, are you?
* '''Gillie Groats:''' With how bad it looks, you wouldn't be any competition to us.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' However, I wonder if I'd be doing a public service by protecting anyone else from it.
* '''Player:''' Is there anything more I could do to convince you?
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Now that you mention it, I've had an incredibly aggressive bull disrupting my herd lately. I've got him caught in the pen over there.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Perhaps you'd be interested in dealing with him? I'd owe you a fairly large favour.
* '''Player:''' A roughly permit sized favour?
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Absolutely.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie again===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' How are you getting on with the bull?
* '''Player:''' I'm getting there! He looks quite tough though.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Cassius===
* '''Cassius:''' Has the Duke given us our permit yet?
* '''Player:''' It's become rather complicated, but I am working it out!
* {{tact|end}}

==Facing the bull==
* {{tselect|Release the bull?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** {{tbox|The bull enters. The cows scatter.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Yes, and don't ask again.}}
** {{tbox|The bull enters. The cows scatter.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===After killing Brutus===
* {{tbox|You notice a strange tag float to the ground as the bull falls. It reads 'Brutus'.}}
* {{mes|You notice a strange tag float to the ground as the bull falls. It reads 'Brutus'.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to open the gate again===
* '''Player:''' Brutus has already been dealt with.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' You succeeded! I'll let the Duke know that you're all good to start a milk business.
* '''Player:''' I don't think that's going to be necessary anymore.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Oh? What happened in that field?
* '''Player:''' That bull was Cassius' other business partner, Brutus.
* '''Player:''' I'm sure he won't be feeling particularly friendly once I let him know.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' That bull was one of the business partners?
* '''Gillie Groats:''' I wonder if his aggression is why Cassius' herd are producing such bad milk...
* '''Player:''' I'm starting to think Cassius doesn't even have his own herd.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' You think he's been stealing milk?
* '''Player:''' I'm not sure where else he would've been getting it from.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Why don't you go and talk to him about it! He may appreciate knowing the{{sic|Should be 'that' not 'the'}} Brutus was bad for business.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie again===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Thank you once again for handling Brutus, he was causing quite a problem for my herd.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' And, if you haven't yet spoken to Cassius, you should probably let him know what's transpired.
* {{tact|end}}

===Returning to Cassius===
* '''Player:''' Cassius, I don't think we'll be getting our business permit.
* '''Cassius:''' Why? What's happened?
* '''Player:''' Brutus is dead.
* '''Cassius:''' Dead?
* '''Cassius:''' How could this have happened?
* '''Player:''' So the Duke asked me to... and then Gillie said that...
* '''Cassius:''' You?!
* '''Cassius:''' Don't tell me you killed Brutus and ruined my- our, plan?
* '''Player:''' In my defence, I had no idea that was Brutus! You made it sound like he was a business partner.
* '''Player:''' Not to mention, apparently his aggression was ruining Seth's herd's milk. This should be a good thing!
* '''Cassius:''' Ruining the milk? The unique flavour was what I was trying to sell!
* '''Cassius:''' You should leave. I can't even look at you.
* {{qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}

==Post-quest==
===Talking to Cassius===
* {{tbox|Cassius makes a point of ignoring you.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Oh, just the person I wanted to see! I have something for you.
* {{tcond|With a full inventory:}}
** '''Gillie Groats:''' Ah, your inventory is full. Can you make some room?
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Gillie Groats:''' This is for helping out with that bull. Our cows are much happier these days.
* {{tbox|pic=Cowbell amulet (empty) detail.png|Gillie hands you an amulet with a bell on it.}}
* '''Gillie Groats:''' One of our local milk enjoyers gave us some enchanted cow bells.
* '''Gillie Groats:''' They seem to be quite versatile, enjoy!
* '''Player:''' Wow, thank you! I'll make sure to check it out.
* {{tcond|With a full inventory:}}
** '''Gillie Groats:''' I also have something else for you but your inventory is full. Can you make some room?
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|With free inventory space:}}
** '''Gillie Groats:''' I also have this for you!
** {{tbox|pic=Magic lamp (The Ides of Milk) detail.png|Gillie hands you a magical lamp.}}
** '''Player:''' Oh, thank you!
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie again if the player doesn't have the lamp and hasn't used it yet===
* '''Gillie Groats:''' I have this for you!
* {{tcond|With a full inventory:}}
** '''Gillie Groats:''' Ah, your inventory is full. Can you make some room?
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Magic lamp (The Ides of Milk) detail.png|Gillie hands you a magical lamp.}}
* '''Player:''' Oh, thank you!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gillie without a cowbell amulet===
* '''Player:''' I've lost that amulet you gave me...
* '''Gillie Groats:''' Oh, no worries, here's another.
* {{tbox|pic=Cowbell amulet (empty) detail.png|Gillie hands you an amulet with a bell on it.}}
* '''Player:''' Thank you so much!
* '''Gillie Groats:''' No problem.
* {{tact|end}}
